com.sap.cloud.sdk.s4hana.connectivity.rfc

Class RfcQueryResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sap.cloud.sdk.s4hana.connectivity.rfc.RfcQueryResult
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    QueryResult<RfcQuery,RfcQueryResult>, Iterable<ResultElement>

    public class RfcQueryResult
extends Object
    Class representing the result of a call to a remote-enabled function module (RFC module) returned by RfcQuery .

    Use the methods get(String), get(int), getIfPresent(String), collect(String), size(), isEmpty(), or has(String) to access the content of the RfcQueryResult.

    Use the methods hasFailed(), hasSuccessMessages(), hasInformationMessages(), hasWarningMessages(), or hasErrorMessages() to inspect the resulting messages from the RFM call.
